<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFECFFC6FF6BFB6BFB91FEA3" lastPageId="55" lastPageNumber="330" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFECFFC7FF6BFB6BFCC1FA54" blockId="54.[151,1127,1165,1604]" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFECFFC7FF6BFB6BFEB8FB14" bold="true" box="[151,262,1165,1188]" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFECFFC7FEF3FB6BFE7DFB14" author="BOHEMAN" box="[271,451,1165,1188]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" refId="ref47980" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1857: Catalogue of Coleopterous Insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part IX. Cassidae. Printed by Order of the trustees [of the British Museum], London, 225 pp." type="book" year="1857">BOHEMAN (1857)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFECFFC7FDC7FB6BFC3EFB14" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[571,896,1165,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureomarginata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFECFFC7FDC7FB6BFC3EFB14" box="[571,896,1165,1188]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">Mesomphalia aureomarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the material of Deyrolle, which latter purchased by J. S. Baly. This taxon was enigmatic to subsequent authors and 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFECFFC7FEE5FB2BFE0EFB54" author="SPAETH" box="[281,432,1229,1252]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH (1914)</bibRefCitation>
informally synonymized it with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFECFFC7FCF1FB2BFB95FB54" authority="(Klug, 1829)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[781,1067,1229,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festiva">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFECFFC7FCF1FB2BFC25FB54" box="[781,923,1229,1252]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">Stolas festiva</emphasis>
(Klug, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
as he considered 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFECFFC7FEEEFB0BFE5CFAB4" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[274,482,1261,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureomarginata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFECFFC7FEEEFB0BFE5CFAB4" box="[274,482,1261,1284]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">M. aureomarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
an aberration of the latter species. However, he most likely based his act on primary description only as the actual type specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFECFFC7FC64FAEBFBD8FA94" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[920,1126,1293,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureomarginata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFECFFC7FC64FAEBFBD8FA94" box="[920,1126,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">M. aureomarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was unknown to subsequent authors and the taxon was listed only in catalogues (see BOROWIEC 1999a). 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFECFFC7FEC0FAABFE52FAD4" author="BOHEMAN" box="[316,492,1357,1380]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" refId="ref47980" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1857: Catalogue of Coleopterous Insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part IX. Cassidae. Printed by Order of the trustees [of the British Museum], London, 225 pp." type="book" year="1857">BOHEMAN (1857)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention how many specimens he had at his disposal. However, he presumably had just a singleton, as he gave a single length measurement and did not keep a duplicate. Nevertheless, Deyrolle was a famous insect dealer and it is possible that he actually had more specimens. I therefore designate the BMNH specimen as 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFECFFC7FBF9FA4BFBD9FA74" box="[1029,1127,1453,1476]" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">lectotype</typeStatus>
in order to conserve its identity for the purpose of the new synonymy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFECFFC6FF49FA0BFB91FEA3" blockId="54.[151,1127,1165,1604]" lastBlockId="55.[113,1089,220,307]" lastPageId="55" lastPageNumber="330" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFECFFC7FF49FA0BFEC7F9B4" author="BOROWIEC" box="[181,377,1517,1540]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" pagination="427 - 438" refId="ref48309" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 b: New species of the genera Stolas Billb. and Nebraspis Spaeth (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus 10: 427 - 438." type="journal article" year="1999" yearSuffix="b">BOROWIEC (1999b)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFECFFC7FE10FA0BFC15F9B4" authority="Borowiec, 1999" authorityName="Borowiec" authorityYear="1999" box="[492,939,1517,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Nebraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridimetallica">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFECFFC7FE10FA0BFD45F9B4" box="[492,763,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">Nebraspis viridimetallica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFECFFC7FCFEFA0BFC15F9B4" author="Borowiec" bookContentInfo="476 pp." box="[770,939,1517,1540]" firstAuthor="Borowiec" journalOrPublisher="Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." title="A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="book" year="1999">Borowiec, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a third species of that genus distinctly separated from its two congeners by the metallic elytra and noted its superficial similarity in colouration to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFECFFC7FD0FF9CBFCEBF9F4" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[755,853,1581,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="festiva">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFECFFC7FD0FF9CBFCEBF9F4" box="[755,853,1581,1604]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="329">S. festiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. However, this taxon is identical to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFEDFFC6FE86FF3AFDF7FF43" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1857" box="[378,585,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureomarginata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFEDFFC6FE86FF3AFDF7FF43" box="[378,585,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="330">M. aureomarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore I restore species status of the latter, transfer it to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFEDFFC6FE9AFF1AFDDAFEA3" authority="Spaeth, 1913" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1913" box="[358,612,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Nebraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFEDFFC6FE9AFF1AFE6CFEA3" box="[358,466,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="330">Nebraspis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFEDFFC6FE25FF1AFDDAFEA3" author="Spaeth" box="[473,612,252,275]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="55" pageNumber="330" pagination="126 - 164" refId="ref50967" refString="SPAETH F. 1913: Kritische Studien uber den Umfang und die Begrenzung mehrerer Cassiden-Gattungen nebst Beschreibung neuer amerik. Arten. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 79: 126 - 164." type="journal article" year="1913">Spaeth, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFEDFFC6FCDCFF1AFC62FEA3" authorityName="Borowiec" authorityYear="1999" box="[800,988,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Nebraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridimetallica">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFEDFFC6FCDCFF1AFC62FEA3" box="[800,988,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="330">N. viridimetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
